io.sarl.sre.network.services

Class HazelcastEventTransportService

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.sarl.sre.network.services.HazelcastEventTransportService
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EventTransportService

    @Singleton
public class HazelcastEventTransportService
extends Object
implements EventTransportService
    Implementation of a MTS using Hazeclast topics to distribute messages over a network of SARL's SREs. For EventSpace, the Hazelcast topics' messages contains events

    Topics' naming conventions (based on io.sarl.api.naming):

    • Context: io.sarl.topics.context.contextId
    • Space: io.sarl.topics.space.contextId.spaceId
    • Agent: io.sarl.topics.agent.contextId.spaceId.agentId
    • Skill: io.sarl.topics.skill.contextId.spaceId.agentId.capacityType
    • Behavior: io.sarl.topics.behavior.contextId.spaceId.agentId.behaviorType.behaviorIndex
    • Skill: io.sarl.topics.service.serviceType

      • routeEvent

        public def routeEvent(event : Event,
                      space : EventSpace,
                      scope : Scope<? super Address>) : boolean 
        Description copied from interface: EventTransportService
        Manages events transmission, deciding when to forward it on the network or/and to route it locally

        Locally, this function emits the event only on the internal event bus of the listeners.

        Locally, this function launches a task for each matching listener.

        Specified by:
        routeEvent in interface EventTransportService
        Parameters:
        event - the event to emit.
        scope - description of the scope of the event, i.e. the receivers of the event.
        Returns:
        true if the message should be also routed locally by the space instance itself. false if the space instance must not route the event.
